{"issue_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/5329", "repo": "rails", "body": "```ruby\r\n# returns true or false\r\ndef has_name\r\n  (first_name && last_name).present?\r\nend\r\n```\r\n\r\nJust an example of using `#present?` which always returns true or false. I understand your argument of whether it should be *guaranteed* to return a boolean or just work in a conditional statement, but again it did break API compatibility and it looks stylistically ugly to some of us to return a non-boolean value.", "_id": {"$oid": "523819bdbd3543c15100e201"}, "issue_id": 5329, "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/comments/4669164", "html_url": "https://github.com/rails/rails/pull/5329#issuecomment-4669164", "updated_at": "2012-03-23T22:33:18Z", "user": {"subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/clifton/subscriptions", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/clifton/events{/privacy}", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/clifton/repos", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/clifton/gists{/gist_id}", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/clifton", "login": "clifton", "gravatar_id": "4cede21ea96795d2de831e9981cc81cd", "html_url": "https://github.com/clifton", "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/clifton/following{/other_user}", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/clifton/received_events", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/clifton/orgs", "avatar_url": "https://1.gravatar.com/avatar/4cede21ea96795d2de831e9981cc81cd?d=https%3A%2F%2Fidenticons.github.com%2Fc27181a18d3b30d14d66a1a56c068548.png", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/clifton/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "id": 14217, "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/clifton/followers", "type": "User"}, "created_at": "2012-03-23T22:33:18Z", "id": 4669164, "owner": "rails"}
